{{head|fr|conjunction}}

# [[once]], [[as soon as]]
#* '''2018''', Zaz, ''on s'en remet jamais''
#*: {{quote|fr| Est-ce que tout ce que l'on se promet a pu se perdre dans un désert ? Ne reste-t-il que des poussières '''une fois que''' l'amour est absent.|Could everything we hoped for have been lost in a desert? Nothing but dust remains '''once''' the love is lost.}}
## {{n-g|With {{m|fr|que}}, introducing a full clause in the perfect aspect.}}
##: {{uxi|fr|'''Une fois''' qu'elle l'aura vu, elle le comprendra.|t='''Once''' she’s seen it, she'll understand it.}}
## {{n-g|Introducing a reduced passive-voice clause consisting only of a subject plus a past participle phrase.}}
##: {{uxi|fr|'''Une fois''' le déjeuner fini, vous pourrez remonter.|t='''Once''' dinner is finished, you can go up.}}
## {{n-g|Introducing a reduced perfect-aspect clause consisting only of a subject plus a past participle phrase (provided that the verb is one that forms the perfect aspect with {{m|fr|être}}).}}
##: {{uxi|fr|'''Une fois''' les professeurs arrivés, les élèves expliquèrent tout.|t='''Once''' the teachers had arrived, the students explained everything.}}
## {{n-g|Introducing a reduced clause in either of the above senses, consisting only a past participle phrase, its subject being implied.}}
##: {{ux|fr|'''Une fois''' sortie de cette maison, elle se sentit libérée.|t='''Once''' she was out of that house, she felt liberated.}}

